article.description: Garrison Matthews scored 15 points and his final five points in the last 50 seconds lifted Lipscomb over Jacksonville 93-92 Thursday night.
article.headline: Lipscomb upends Jacksonville 93-92
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Garrison Matthews scored 15 points and his final five points in the last 50 seconds lifted Lipscomb over Jacksonville 93-92 Thursday night. Matthews-who also had 10 rebounds-hit two free throws, and his 3-point play off a layup gave Lipscomb a 91-89 lead with seven seconds to go. Lipscomb (9-18, 5-5 Atlantic Sun) shot 9 for 11 from the free throw line in the final 2:14. The Dolphins committed six fouls during that span. Jacksonville led 85-82 on J.R. Holder's jumper with 2:34 to play. Holder then fouled Cam Miller, who hit two free throws, and the play triggered a parade of Bisons to the free throw line. Kori Babineaux and Marcel White each scored for Jacksonville, which led 89-86 with a minute left. White scored 28 and Babineaux added 25 for Jacksonville (15-12, 7-3). Eli Pepper led the Bisons with 19 points, Nathan Moran had 18, and J.C. Hampton chipped in 17 for Lipscomb.
